import React, { useEffect, useRef } from 'react'; import './web.css'; function Web() { const textRef = useRef(null); const phrases = [ "Welcome to my portfolio.", "I'm a software developer.", "Let's build something amazing!" ]; let phraseIndex = 0; let letterIndex = 0; useEffect(() => { let typingInterval; const typeText = () => { typingInterval = setInterval(() => { if (letterIndex < phrases[phraseIndex].length) { textRef.current.textContent += phrases[phraseIndex].charAt(letterIndex); letterIndex++; } else { clearInterval(typingInterval); setTimeout(() => { eraseText(); }, 2000); // Wait before erasing } }, 100); }; const eraseText = () => { const eraseInterval = setInterval(() => { if (letterIndex > 0) { textRef.current.textContent = textRef.current.textContent.slice(0, -1); letterIndex--; } else { clearInterval(eraseInterval); phraseIndex = (phraseIndex + 1) % phrases.length; setTimeout(() => { typeText(); }, 500); } }, 50); }; typeText(); // Start typing when component mounts return () => clearInterval(typingInterval); // Cleanup on component unmount }, [phrases]); return ( <>

My journey in the tech world began with a curiosity to understand how things work, which led me to pursue a career in software development.
